description: Python type hint standards for fully typed, mypy-strict codebases
alwaysApply: true
---

python-type-safety:

- All function parameters and return types must have type annotations
- Never use bare `dict`, `list`, `tuple` - use `dict[str, Any]`, `list[int]`, `tuple[str, ...]`
- Use `Optional[X]` or `X | None` for nullable values - never leave unannotated
- Prefer `TypedDict` or Pydantic models over plain `dict` for structured data
- Use `Protocol` for duck typing instead of `Any`
- Enable mypy strict mode: `--strict` flag in mypy.ini
- Never use `# type: ignore` without a comment explaining why
- Use `Final` for constants, `ClassVar` for class-level attributes
- Use `Literal` types for string enums instead of plain `str`
- Run mypy in CI - type errors must block merges
